fields.description: The custom authentication strength enforced in a Conditional Access policy.
fields.name: AuthenticationStrength

fields.description: Refers to the conditional access policy conditions that aren't satisfied. The possible values are: none, application, users, devicePlatform, location, clientType, signInRisk, userRisk, time, deviceState, client,ipAddressSeenByAzureAD,ipAddressSeenByResourceProvider,unknownFutureValue,servicePrincipals,servicePrincipalRisk, authenticationFlows, insiderRisk . Use the Prefer: include-unknown-enum-members request header to get the following values in this evolvable enum: servicePrincipals,servicePrincipalRisk, authenticationFlows, insiderRisk. conditionalAccessConditions is a multi-valued enumeration and the property can contain multiple values in a comma-separated list.
fields.name: ConditionsNotSatisfied

fields.description: Refers to the conditional access policy conditions that are satisfied. The possible values are: none, application, users, devicePlatform, location, clientType, signInRisk, userRisk, time, deviceState, client,ipAddressSeenByAzureAD,ipAddressSeenByResourceProvider,unknownFutureValue,servicePrincipals,servicePrincipalRisk, authenticationFlows, insiderRisk. Use the Prefer: include-unknown-enum-members request header to get the following values in this evolvable enum: servicePrincipals,servicePrincipalRisk, authenticationFlows, insiderRisk. conditionalAccessConditions is a multi-valued enumeration and the property can contain multiple values in a comma-separated list.
fields.name: ConditionsSatisfied

fields.description: Name of the conditional access policy.
fields.name: DisplayName

fields.description: Refers to the grant controls enforced by the conditional access policy (example: 'Require multifactor authentication').
fields.name: EnforcedGrantControls

fields.description: Refers to the session controls enforced by the conditional access policy (example: 'Require app enforced controls').
fields.name: EnforcedSessionControls

fields.description: List of key-value pairs containing each matched exclude condition in the conditional access policy. Example: [{'devicePlatform' : 'DevicePlatform'}] means the policy didn't apply, because the DevicePlatform condition was a match.
fields.name: ExcludeRulesSatisfied

fields.description: Identifier of the conditional access policy.
fields.name: Id

fields.description: List of key-value pairs containing each matched include condition in the conditional access policy. Example: [{ 'application' : 'AllApps'}, {'users': 'Group'}], meaning Application condition was a match because AllApps are included and Users condition was a match because the user was part of the included Group rule.
fields.name: IncludeRulesSatisfied

fields.description: The OData ID of this entity
fields.name: ODataId

fields.description: The OData Type of this entity
fields.name: ODataType

fields.description: Indicates the result of the CA policy that was triggered. Possible values are: success, failure, notApplied (policy isn't applied because policy conditions weren't met), notEnabled (this is due to the policy in a disabled state), unknown, unknownFutureValue, reportOnlySuccess, reportOnlyFailure, reportOnlyNotApplied, reportOnlyInterrupted. Use the Prefer: include-unknown-enum-members request header to get the following values in this evolvable enum: reportOnlySuccess, reportOnlyFailure, reportOnlyNotApplied, reportOnlyInterrupted.
fields.name: Result

fields.description: Refers to the session controls that a sign-in activity didn't satisfy. (Example: Application enforced Restrictions).
fields.name: SessionControlsNotSatisfied
